th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde de Bernatre was born in 1171. She had at least 1 son with Hugues de Gorenflos. She died in 1237, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1190–1254":"1190–1254","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"1159","1254":"1254","1171":"1171","1218":"1218"},"fi":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1190–1254":"1190–1254","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"1159","1254":"1254","1171":"1171","1218":"1218"},"fr":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1190–1254":"1190–1254","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"1159","1254":"1254","1171":"1171","1218":"1218","lifeSummary":"Mathilde de Bernatre est née en 1171. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Hugues de Gorenflos. Elle est décédée en 1237, à l’âge de 66 ans."},"de":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1190–1254":"1190–1254","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"1159","1254":"1254","1171":"1171","1218":"1218","lifeSummary":"Mathilde de Bernatre wurde 1171 geboren. Sie hatte mit Hugues de Gorenflos mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1237 im Alter von 66 Jahren."},"ht":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1190–1254":"1190–1254","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"1159","1254":"1254","1171":"1171","1218":"1218"},"hu":{"1171–1237":"1171–1237","1159–1218":"1159–1218"